result.execSummary:
The defendant Frederick Marshall Wynn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-Sexual Contact, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Frederick Marshall Wynn in court, in custody.  Attorney Kerri Terann Cleghorn in court for Frederick Marshall Wynn.  Attorney Erin Michelle Karshen in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Sentencing proceeds. As to the presentence investigation report - no corrections however State notes there were referrals that charges were not processed.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.

Back on the record; same appearances.
Sentencing hearing continues:

As to Count  1:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  15   years  -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  9  years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  6  years.  

As to Count 2:  
Court sentenced defendant to serve 266  DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for  266 days; TIME SERVED.  

Court finds defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program after 7 and 1/2 years of initial confinement has been served.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION: 
-  Sex Offender evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment and/or therapy
-  Work towards obtaining literacy
-  No Contact with the victim
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  Maintain compliance with the Sex Offender Registry for a period of 15 years
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis and pay the surcharge (if not already done so) during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at a rate (to be determined by DOC) of prison funds

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Pretrial Incarceration Credit, and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.

Defendant Frederick Marshall Wynn in court with Attorney Kerri Terann Cleghorn.  Defendant Frederick Marshall Wynn in custody.  Erin Michelle Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  All parties appear in person.

COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms; further, defendant is advised he cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  Defendant was further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible.
